//
// T031 — R4 bit-slice and concat spacing per formatting-rules.contract.md §4.
//
// Frozen invariants:
//   * bit slice: `a[7:0]` — no spaces inside `[`, `]`, around `:`
//   * concat:    `{a, b, c}` — one space after each `,`, no spaces
//                 inside `{`, `}` (unless `spaces_inside_braces=true`)
//
// AUTHORED RED — XFAIL until T050 implements R4. Removing XFAIL
// is a checkpoint of the implementation's correctness.

// XFAIL: *
// RUN: echo 'module m { wire d = a[ 7 : 0 ]; wire e = {a , b , c}; }' | nsl-fmt --stdin | FileCheck %s
// CHECK: a[7:0]
// CHECK-SAME: {a, b, c}
